<paragraph id="8B82EE275F41FFA6FF26738919AE44F8" blockId="1.[151,1436,1438,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
The genus may be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D95A45F41FFA6FDEC73891BFA47C0" box="[605,698,1438,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Alebrini">Alebrini</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of features: forewing appendix not extended around apical margin, all apical cells much longer than broad, parallel-sided, and angular basally, with bases (except first) alligned; hind wing with submarginal vein distinct, free from apical margin and confluent with 
<collectingCountry id="F32AAEB75F41FFA6FF26701C19FD4454" box="[151,189,1547,1570]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">RP</collectingCountry>
; vein CuP confluent with submarginal vein near midlength of wing, much basad of vein m-cu; male style sigmoid in lateral aspect; aedeagus shaft with one or two pairs of apical or anteapical processes; sternal abdominal apodemes slender and elongate, usually capitate apically, traversing one or two abdominal conjunctivae (Young 
<number id="3DF5FC005F41FFA6FF267061199244F8" box="[151,210,1654,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" value="1957.0">1957</number>
b).
</paragraph>
